00:13:59.219 --> 00:14:06.340
and continuous deployment. So that involves automating the process of deployment. So any

00:14:06.340 --> 00:14:11.859
time you make any code changes, it will, you know, as with any automation, will save time.

00:14:11.859 --> 00:14:17.659
You don't have to redeploy it every time you make a code change. So yeah, this will

00:14:17.659 --> 00:14:21.580
help save time.

00:14:21.580 --> 00:14:26.539
Another strategy is containerization, and that involves packaging your app and its dependencies

00:14:26.539 --> 00:14:32.820
into isolated environments known as containers. This approach ensures consistent behavior

00:14:32.820 --> 00:14:36.940
across different environments from, like, development to production. So, like, you can

00:14:36.940 --> 00:14:42.340
encapsulate, like, your environment variables and things like that all into the Docker container.

